==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electro-polar
<hw>E*lec`tro-po"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Possessing electrical polarity; positively
electrified at one end, or on one surface, and negatively at the other;
-- said of a conductor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-positive</ent>⟦br⟧
